  "text": "With the advent of Intelligent Transportation System (ITS) [CITATION_1] , automobile companies have started deploying more Electronic Control Units (ECUs) in vehicles for engine management, air bag controlling, automatic brake systems and air condition control. Along with these enhancements the increase in vehicles on roads and streets has also made it compulsory to implement safety applications for vehicles. Vehicular Ad Hoc Networks (VANETs) [CITATION_2] are gaining scope because they are providing numerous applications like traffic safety, driver assistance, entertainment, internet access, automatic toll payment and many more for roadside environments.",
